[2026-01-21 18:36:18] [INFO] Full LLM response:
The lemma `IsStarProjection_iff` corresponds to the standard characterization of star projections in a Hilbert space, which relates self-adjoint idempotents (star projections) to orthogonal projections onto submodules. This result has been formalized in Mathlib (likely in the PR #25958 mentioned) as `ContinuousLinearMap.isStarProjection_iff`.

```lean
lemma IsStarProjection_iff (p : H →L[ℂ] H) : IsStarProjection p ↔ ∃ (K : Submodule ℂ H),
    ∃ (kH : K.HasOrthogonalProjection), p = K.subtypeL.comp (@K.orthogonalProjection _ _ _ _ _ kH)
  := ContinuousLinearMap.isStarProjection_iff
```
