[2026-01-21 18:36:28] [INFO] Full LLM response:
The code contains a lemma `IsStarProjection_iff` which states that a continuous linear map `p` is a star projection (self-adjoint idempotent) if and only if it is the orthogonal projection onto some submodule `K`. This result is available in Mathlib as `ContinuousLinearMap.isStarProjection_iff_exists_orthogonalProjection`, which was introduced in the PR mentioned in the comment.

```lean
lemma IsStarProjection_iff (p : H →L[ℂ] H) : IsStarProjection p ↔ ∃ (K : Submodule ℂ H),
    ∃ (kH : K.HasOrthogonalProjection), p = K.subtypeL.comp (@K.orthogonalProjection _ _ _ _ _ kH)
  := ContinuousLinearMap.isStarProjection_iff_exists_orthogonalProjection p
```
